The paper proposes a new theory for visual-inertial navigation systems, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also extensively uses computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for feature extraction and image alignment. The paper involves optimization and estimation techniques (cs.LG) for state estimation. The paper also involves control systems (cs.SY) for navigation. Finally, the paper involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI) for loop closure detection.
